<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881014-0048 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief -- Instrument Systems Corp.: Firm to Buy Eaton Corp.'s Command Systems Division </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ISY ETN </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Instrument Systems Corp. said it agreed to acquire the command systems division of Eaton Corp., Cleveland. The division, with $50 million in annual sales, makes air traffic control systems and other systems for civilian and military applications.    The price wasn't disclosed. Instrument Systems, Jericho, N.Y., makes electronic gear, specialty plastic films, home furnishings and apparel.    Eaton said the sale fits with its intention to focus resources on its vehicle power train and electronics and controls business areas. </TEXT></DOC>